  "notes": "Headline axes: FIRST N (head_n) limit syntax from Informix/Firebird tradition, double-quoted string literals, upper-case-folded double-quoted identifiers, MINUS for EXCEPT, UNIQUE for DISTINCT, and sole <> not-equal. The || concat is pure string-only (no implicit type coercion). Double-quote serves dual duty for strings and identifiers, resolved by parser context (identifier quoting uses double quotes around identifiers in FROM/JOIN/GROUP BY positions; string literals use double quotes in value positions).",
